"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-31-olympics-2024-stop-bad-mouthing-super-falcons-ayinde-rallies-support-for-teammates\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Halimat Ayinde has rallied support for her Super Falcons teammates ahead of the crunch Group C clash with Japan.  The Super Falcons must beat the Asian champions to have any chance of making it to the quarter-finals at the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games.  Randy Waldrum's side lost their opening two games against Brazil and Spain.  Ayinde, who missed out on a place in the Super Falcons squad to the Olympics due to injury also challenged the players to give their all on the pitch.  \\\"Stop the bad-mouthing and give the Super Falcons all the support they need today.One love. Let us give everything today mates, \\\" she wrote on X.  The encounter slated for the Stade de la Beaujoire, Nantes will kick-off at 4pm Nigeria time.  Adamu pens two-year contract with Katsina United  He's humble, good player - Jorginho on Arsenal's latest signing  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"